===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|lepen}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|hlēapan}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*hlaupaną}} (compare {{etyl|fy|-}} {{m|fy|ljeppe}} ‘to jump’, Dutch {{m|nl|lopen}} ‘to run; to walk’, German {{m|de|laufen}} ‘to run; to walk’, Danish {{m|en|løbe}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*klAub-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*klAup-||to spring, stumble}} (compare Lithuanian {{m|lt|šlùbti}} ‘to become lame’, {{m|lt|klùbti}} ‘to stumble’).

