#: ''to '''leap''' a horse across a ditch''

=====Usage notes=====
The choice between {{m|en|leapt}} and {{m|en|leaped}} is mostly a matter of regional differences: {{m|en|leapt}} is preferred in British English and {{m|en|leaped}} in American English. According to research by John Algeo (''British or American English?'', Cambridge, 2006), {{m|en|leapt}} is used 80% of the time in UK and 32% in the US.

